1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,680
NAMNUNG: Some people start as strangers.

2
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:04,200
SUNNY: Some start as friends.

3
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:06,120
SUNNY: But some start as enemies.

4
00:00:06,120 --> 00:00:07,360
NAMNUNG: And what if one day...

5
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:09,680
SUNNY: That enemy becomes someone
we're forbidden to love.

6
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:11,720
NAMNUNG: Very intense.

7
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:13,840
SUNNY: Welcome back to Girls' Secret Party.

8
00:00:13,840 --> 00:00:15,840
SUNNY: Episode 2 with SUNNY and NAMNUNG.

9
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:19,160
NAMNUNG: Girls just wanna have some fun.

10
00:00:19,160 --> 00:00:21,960
NAMNUNG: I'm really excited to discuss new topics.

11
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:24,880
NAMNUNG: We've had a bit of an intro.
What's our main topic?

12
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:26,120
SUNNY: Forbidden love.

13
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,200
SUNNY: Love that's forbidden.

14
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,360
NAMNUNG: Forbidden love is kind of like...

15
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,080
SUNNY: Scandal.

16
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:32,720
NAMNUNG: Yeah, we like toxic things. It's kind of...

17
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:33,280
SUNNY: You like it?

18
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:34,000
NAMNUNG: No.

19
00:00:34,592 --> 00:00:35,840
NAMNUNG: But sometimes it's like

20
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:38,120
NAMNUNG: everyone has a bit of a toxic side in them.

21
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:39,320
- NAMNUNG: There has to be a bit.
- SUNNY: I got it.

22
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:42,640
NAMNUNG: This is the point
that triggers us to do something.

23
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:43,760
NAMNUNG: Today we have another game.

24
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:45,720
NAMNUNG: It's about asking questions.

25
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:49,080
NAMNUNG: If we had to date our enemy, what would we do?

26
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:52,040
NAMNUNG: As mentioned in the intro today.

27
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:53,400
NAMNUNG: Who wants to go first with a question?

28
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,040
SUNNY: Go ahead.

29
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:55,040
NAMNUNG: Sure.

30
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:58,200
NAMNUNG: If you had to date your enemy

31
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,400
NAMNUNG: or someone you dislike for a day,
how would you survive it?

32
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:02,400
SUNNY: Let's just see who's the bigger villain.

33
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:03,200
SUNNY: Tit for tat.

34
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,480
NAMNUNG: Very toxic.

35
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,960
SUNNY: We don't like each other, but sometimes

36
00:01:05,960 --> 00:01:07,280
SUNNY: being mean and being mean back is kind of...

37
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,320
NAMNUNG: This can be killing.

38
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:11,640
NAMNUNG: If I'm going to make it through a date,

39
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,600
NAMNUNG: I need someone playful and witty. You know.

40
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:15,840
NAMNUNG: Someone I can have
some back-and-forth banter with.

41
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,120
NAMNUNG: It feels like breaking the ice.

42
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,680
NAMNUNG: But if I don't truly like them,

43
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:19,760
NAMNUNG: it's best we stay out of each other's way.

44
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:20,880
- SUNNY: But you have to go on a date.
- NAMNUNG: Alone...

45
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,000
NAMNUNG: Alone together, you know.

46
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,280
NAMNUNG: Suppose it's something work-related.

47
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,240
NAMNUNG: I don't like this person.

48
00:01:24,240 --> 00:01:26,760
NAMNUNG: But I have to work with them
and pretend to like them.

49
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:28,640
NAMNUNG: We can fake it, you know?

50
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:31,280
NAMNUNG: We're professionals when it comes to acting.

51
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,280
NAMNUNG: Next question?

52
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,920
SUNNY: Working in a group with your
most hated person for a month,

53
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:36,160
SUNNY: is there a chance of falling in love?

54
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:38,600
NAMNUNG: Is it possible? Maybe.

55
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,480
NAMNUNG: Suppose previously
we just casually disliked each other.

56
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,680
NAMNUNG: We just didn't like each other's faces.

57
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:45,280
NAMNUNG: But working in a group
might give us time to communicate more.

58
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,880
NAMNUNG: We might see many things differently.

59
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,320
NAMNUNG: It might develop into something.

60
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,360
SUNNY: I think...

61
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:50,960
SUNNY: I'd probably fail that group work.

62
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:51,920
NAMNUNG: Argue?

63
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,280
SUNNY: Whatever I say must be right.

64
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,600
NAMNUNG: Then is it group work?

65
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,600
SUNNY: Isn't this group work just two people?

66
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:57,760
NAMNUNG: Suppose the group work is just two people.

67
00:01:57,760 --> 00:02:00,320
SUNNY: There might be moments like...
Our first episode... That's like...

68
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:03,240
SUNNY: Boring, lying on hands.

69
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:06,120
NAMNUNG: Impossible.

70
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:09,120
SUNNY: I think love might not happen for me.

71
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:10,080
NAMNUNG: But there might be feelings for each other.

72
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:12,360
SUNNY: We might not like each other's personalities.

73
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:15,800
SUNNY: But if we look at it from
the co-working perspective,

74
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:18,520
SUNNY: I don't like you
because your people have bad manners.

75
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,320
SUNNY: But you're good at work.

76
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,760
SUNNY: I might like you from a work perspective.

77
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,800
SUNNY: But I don't like you as a person.

78
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,800
NAMNUNG: That makes sense.

79
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,840
SUNNY: Just compartmentalize.
Get the job done and never talk again.

80
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,640
NAMNUNG: There's a lot of possibility.

81
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:33,720
NAMNUNG: If you have issues, and they apologize first.

82
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,400
NAMNUNG: They apologize, and then
go right back to being cheeky.

83
00:02:35,400 --> 00:02:36,680
NAMNUNG: Will you forgive?

84
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,440
SUNNY: I think if I truly hate someone...

85
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:40,280
SUNNY: Whatever they do, it's like, whatever.

86
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,920
SUNNY: Whether they apologize or not, I feel the same.

87
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,320
NAMNUNG: Just approaching us makes us angry, right?

88
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,040
NAMNUNG: That's already irritating, isn't it?

89
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:46,640
SUNNY: Yes.

90
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:49,680
NAMNUNG: For me? Apologies are whatever.

91
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:52,040
NAMNUNG: But if I don't get along with,
or I dislike someone,

92
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,600
NAMNUNG: I'll ignore them completely.

93
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:55,240
NAMNUNG: Live your life. Don't bother me.

94
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,680
NAMNUNG: And I won't bother you. That's it.

95
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:59,280
NAMNUNG: No fights, no grudges.

96
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:01,240
NAMNUNG: No hitting or fighting, never happened.

97
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:02,480
- NAMNUNG: It's more like the feeling that
- SUNNY: Yeah, I get it.

98
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:05,840
NAMNUNG: I understand. I can feel
that you don't like me.

99
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:07,960
NAMNUNG: I won't bother you
and you shouldn't bother me.

100
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,320
NAMNUNG: But the moment you do,

101
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,400
NAMNUNG: I'm coming for you too. Your call.

102
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,680
SUNNY: Oh, I agree with this.

103
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:14,560
SUNNY: Normally, I'm not the type
to make the first move.

104
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:17,024
- SUNNY: But if you do so, I'll say no.
- NAMNUNG: Yes.

105
00:03:17,024 --> 00:03:17,600
NAMNUNG: No.

106
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,520
SUNNY: I put more effort in.

107
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:19,280
NAMNUNG: No.

108
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,400
NAMNUNG: Basically, don't mess with me
if you don't like me.

109
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,120
NAMNUNG: Don't mess with me.

110
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,600
NAMNUNG: There's a feeling like...

111
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,200
NAMNUNG: Hey.

112
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,480
NAMNUNG: Suppose you don't like me,

113
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:27,400
NAMNUNG: it makes no sense for us to stay connected.

114
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:29,880
NAMNUNG: You don't even have to talk to me.

115
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,640
NAMNUNG: Just remove each other
from our lives for good.

116
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:34,640
NAMNUNG: But if you still want to mess with me,

117
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,320
NAMNUNG: it becomes like... Oh! Or...

118
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,920
NAMNUNG: Is my life better than yours?

119
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,360
- NAMNUNG: You're so interested in me.
- SUNNY: It's jealous.

120
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:42,200
NAMNUNG: Sometimes it's just people on social media

121
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:46,240
NAMNUNG: who don't even know me before. Out of
nowhere, they dislike me and start criticizing me.

122
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,520
NAMNUNG: Do they actually understand my life?

123
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,320
NAMNUNG: Not at all.

124
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,880
NAMNUNG: It's not that I'm angry
when they criticize, but there's a feeling like...

125
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,800
NAMNUNG: Oh, is my life really that good?

126
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,840
- NAMNUNG: It makes someone interested in me that much.
- SUNNY: Even harsher than before.

127
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,640
NAMNUNG: It's like, "Oh, my life is so good."

128
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:02,640
NAMNUNG: "Or is your life just empty
that you're so obsessed with mine?"

129
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:04,160
NAMNUNG: There's more of this kind of feeling.

130
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,840
SUNNY: I can understand that.

131
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,720
SUNNY: Next, between having hated each other before

132
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:12,200
SUNNY: or not knowing at all,
which has a better shot at becoming a couple?

133
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,240
NAMNUNG: Never known each other at all.

134
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:14,200
SUNNY: Makes sense.

135
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:17,440
NAMNUNG: Having hated before means
there's something there

136
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:18,368
NAMNUNG: that we didn't like.

137
00:04:18,368 --> 00:04:18,960
SUNNY: Yes.

138
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:20,840
NAMNUNG: If we like, we date. If not,

139
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:22,640
NAMNUNG: there's no reason to continue.

140
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:25,560
- SUNNY: I couldn't agree more. You said it all.
- NAMNUNG: Yeah. No.

141
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:28,520
NAMNUNG: Can't say anything more. It's very obvious.

142
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:31,840
NAMNUNG: In the past, like in your dating life,

143
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:35,880
NAMNUNG: have you ever done
something dumb for someone that

144
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,960
NAMNUNG: at this point, you feel
you shouldn't have liked them.

145
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:40,280
NAMNUNG: Thinking, "Oh, why did I do it then?"

146
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,840
SUNNY: I've been there.

147
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:45,400
SUNNY: It's been, like,
almost ten years. I'm getting old.

148
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,600
SUNNY: My first love

149
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,840
SUNNY: is when I was in America.

150
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,920
SUNNY: It was a relationship we shouldn't have been in.

151
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:53,200
SUNNY: It was like one day we loved each other.
The next we hated each other.

152
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,920
SUNNY: But because it was very toxic, right?
It was just like ups and downs.

153
00:04:56,920 --> 00:05:00,520
SUNNY: On good days, it was "Yeah!"
On bad days, it was "Oh, here we go again."

154
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,080
SUNNY: But it was just like

155
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:05,040
SUNNY: that we're just competing to see
who can hurt the other more.

156
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:07,240
SUNNY: Today you hurt me,
and tomorrow I'll hurt you back.

157
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:10,800
SUNNY: They hurt me, and I'll show them that
they will get hurt way more than I did.

158
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,880
SUNNY: It just went back and forth like this until...

159
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,840
SUNNY: "What are we doing? We're wasting so much time."

160
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,600
SUNNY: If we were friends,

161
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:18,560
SUNNY: we think alike, so we're toxic alike.

162
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,560
SUNNY: If we were just friends,
would our lives be better than this?

163
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,840
NAMNUNG: Yeah, it fits.

164
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:24,240
NAMNUNG: Toxic with toxic.

165
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,920
NAMNUNG: But for me, I've been there before.

166
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,480
NAMNUNG: It's a past experience like...

167
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:29,400
NAMNUNG: Why did I date someone like that?

168
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,800
SUNNY: Agree. Why?

169
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:33,400
NAMNUNG: SUNNY knows everything very well.

170
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,360
NAMNUNG: We always talk about past relationships.

171
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:38,080
NAMNUNG: I can't mention names. You figure it out.

172
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:41,800
NAMNUNG: It's the thought of what was going on?
What I was infatuated with?

173
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,280
NAMNUNG: Why did I do it then?

174
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,800
NAMNUNG: Why did it have to be this person?

175
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,560
NAMNUNG: Now, looking back,

176
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,280
NAMNUNG: even though we didn't date for long,
I got out quickly.

177
00:05:49,280 --> 00:05:51,040
NAMNUNG: Because I started realizing.

178
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:53,880
- NAMNUNG: But it was like, why did I do that?
- SUNNY: Embarrassing.

179
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:57,400
NAMNUNG: Why do people like this exist in the world?

180
00:05:57,400 --> 00:05:58,680
- NAMNUNG: Oh, that's harsh.
- SUNNY: But...

181
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,040
NAMNUNG: But perhaps still immature, those things.

182
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:03,200
NAMNUNG: Feelings might pass quickly, stuff like that.

183
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:06,240
NAMNUNG: I just ended a long first relationship too.

184
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,680
NAMNUNG: It could be a feeling of loneliness.

185
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:10,000
NAMNUNG: I didn't really
care about them, but I felt like...

186
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,920
NAMNUNG: At that time, I had them,
so it was like okay. This person would do.

187
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,160
NAMNUNG: But,

188
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:17,720
NAMNUNG: it's a lesson not to rush,
better to study it well.

189
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,680
SUNNY: Yes.

190
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,280
NAMNUNG: Live life day by day. People will come anyway.

191
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:22,440
NAMNUNG: No matter when,

192
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:25,000
NAMNUNG: don't rush. If you feel
it's not right, then it's not right.

193
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,280
SUNNY: Agree.

194
00:06:26,280 --> 00:06:27,680
NAMNUNG: We just talked about enemies.

195
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,280
NAMNUNG: If you have to date
an enemy, you won't accept it.

196
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:29,880
SUNNY: Yeah.

197
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,760
NAMNUNG: If I gave you the choice

198
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,960
NAMNUNG: between dating an enemy
and dating a friend's ex.

199
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:35,880
SUNNY: A friend's.

200
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:37,760
SUNNY: I thought you'd stop at just an ex.

201
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:39,200
SUNNY: I was like, "Oh, then date."

202
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,160
NAMNUNG: Your friend's.

203
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:42,400
SUNNY: I think I wouldn't date my friend's ex.

204
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,320
SUNNY: If I did, I would
become enemies with my friends.

205
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:47,320
NAMNUNG: Right, you'll get more enemies.
Isn't it better to stay out of it?

206
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,840
SUNNY: If I had to choose between the two,
I'd probably choose enemies.

207
00:06:49,840 --> 00:06:51,640
NAMNUNG: It's the same. Just feels like...

208
00:06:51,640 --> 00:06:53,680
NAMNUNG: If I had to be involved

209
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:55,160
NAMNUNG: with my friend's ex,

210
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:57,120
NAMNUNG: it won't end well in the end.

211
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,880
- SUNNY: Yeah, with anyone.
- NAMNUNG: Hmm.

212
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:01,480
NAMNUNG: I feel like the relationship won't last long.

213
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,800
NAMNUNG: Because you'll have issues
with your friends and stuff like that.

214
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,680
NAMNUNG: Better to date an enemy.

215
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:09,560
SUNNY: Next question, I'd like to know
about age since you're quite young.

216
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:12,800
SUNNY: What do you think
about age gaps in a relationship?

217
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:13,880
NAMNUNG: Not serious.

218
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:17,480
NAMNUNG: Some people insist on
an age gap of only 2-3 years.

219
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:21,040
NAMNUNG: But I'm very open
since my parents have a 20-year age gap.

220
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,360
NAMNUNG: So it turns out that

221
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:25,520
NAMNUNG: I usually date people who are older.

222
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,280
NAMNUNG: Because I like their mindset.

223
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:27,920
SUNNY: Ah.

224
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,920
NAMNUNG: The way they work,
the way they live, things like that.

